<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <link href="stylesheets/a2style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
    </head>

    <body>
        <h1> TokiDex </h1>

        <p class="p_style">
        Use the following form to insert a new Tokimon into the database!
        <br>
        Keep in mind that if any of the numeric fields are left blank, they will default to 0.
        If either name field is blank, they will stay blank in the database.
        </p>
        <form action="/insert" method="POST">
            <input type="text" name="tokiName" placeholder="Tokimon's Name" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiWeight" placeholder="Tokimon's Weight" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiHeight" placeholder="Tokimon's Height" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiFly" placeholder="Fly Power" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiFight" placeholder="Fight Power" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiFire" placeholder="Fire Power" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiWater" placeholder="Water Power" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiElectric" placeholder="Electric Power" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiIce" placeholder="Ice Power" class="toki_input">
            <input type="text" name="tokiTrainer" placeholder="Trainer's Name" class="toki_input">
            <br> <br>
            <input type="submit" value="Insert Tokimon" class="buttons">
        </form>

        

        <p class="p_style">
            Use the following form to update an existing Tokimon's attributes! 
            Leave the box empty if you would not like to update that attribute. (If the Tokimon doesn't exist, nothing will happen.)
        </p>
    </body>
</html>